    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR6v0299-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0401.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T18:58:21.766+09:00">JŌWA · FIFTH YEAR</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0401.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T18:57:49.829+09:00">SIXTH MOON: 13th DAY [July 8, 838]. At noon</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0401.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T18:58:04.764+09:00">the embassy board­ed the first and fourth ships,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0401.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T18:58:37.933+09:00">but because we did not have a favorable wind,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0401.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T18:58:52.5+09:00">we waited for three days.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0510.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:00:55.443+09:00">17th DAY. In the middle of the night,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0510.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:02:15.871+09:00">At 10 A. M. we reached the sea east of Shiganoshima.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0510.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:01:37.487+09:00">profiting from a stiff wind, we hoisted sail and set the ships in motion.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0510.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:02:28.792+09:00">Because we did not have reliable winds,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0510.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:02:32.636+09:00">we stopped for five days.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0702.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:04:32.966+09:00">22nd DAY. At 6 A. M.,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0702.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:04:51.952+09:00">profiting from a northeast wind, we set out.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0702.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:05:16.512+09:00">We did not again seek a cove,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0702.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:05:48.834+09:00">and on into the night we went in the dark.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:06:43.263+09:00">23rd DAY. At 10 A. M.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:06:54.492+09:00">we reached Ukushima.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:07:06.46+09:00">A northeast wind was blowing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:07:24.34+09:00">Those going and those staying behind took farewell of one another.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:07:45.511+09:00">At 6 P. M.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:07:56.694+09:00">we hoisted sail and set out across the sea.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:08:15.598+09:00">The northeast wind was blow­ing,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:08:26.119+09:00">and on into the night we went in the dark.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0801.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:08:35.343+09:00">The two ships were in contact with each other by fire signals.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:09:17.965+09:00">24th DAY. We saw at a distance the fourth ship going ahead of us,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:09:36.397+09:00">separated from the first ship</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:10:00.981+09:00"> by about thirty li</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:10:26.031+09:00">and going far to the west.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:10:38.894+09:00">The Ambassador for the first time made a drawing of the Bodhisattva Kannon,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:13:19.671+09:00">and the Scholar and Student Monks</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:13:28.736+09:00"> together read scriptures and prayed</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:14:23.614+09:00">At 10 P. M. [the ships] were in contact by fire signals,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:14:39.34+09:00">which were like stars in appearance,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s10" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:14:58.114+09:00">but when dawn came [the fourth ship] was not to be seen.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s11" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:16:06.765+09:00">Although there had been a shift of the wind from the northeast to the southeast,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s12" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:16:24.04+09:00">we were not afraid of drifting from the course.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:17:25.04+09:00">Great bamboos, roots of reeds, cuttlefish, and the like</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s14" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:17:46.571+09:00">drifted along with the billows.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s15" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:18:05.437+09:00">Dropping hooks, we caught and inspected them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s16" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:18:20.637+09:00">Some were living; others were withered.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s17" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:18:38.499+09:00">The color of the sea was light green.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s18" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:18:57.317+09:00">The men all said that we were close to land.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a0920.s19" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:19:50.447+09:00">At 4 P. M. !arge fish followed the ship, disporting themselves.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:22:41.438+09:00">27th DAY. The "flat irons" were struck by a wave and all fell off.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:23:12.562+09:00">Exhausted [egrets] settled down [on the ship] for the night and did not leave.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:24:29.309+09:00">Two or three would fly off to the west</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:26:15.006+09:00">They did this several times.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:26:27.106+09:00">The sea is whitish green.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:26:54.478+09:00">All night men were ordered to mount the mast</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1508.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:27:12.578+09:00">to look for mountains or islands, and they would always call out that they saw none.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s1" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:27:44.815+09:00">28th DAY. Early in the morning</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s2" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:28:06.08+09:00">the egrets flew off in pairs toward the northwest.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s3" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:28:16.791+09:00">Since the wind was still un­changed,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s4" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:28:32.686+09:00">we trimmed sail and headed southwest.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s5" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:28:46.281+09:00">At 10 A. M. we reached whitish water,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s6" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:29:00.312+09:00"> the color of which was like yellow mud.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s7" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:29:25.045+09:00">The men all said</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s8" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:29:49.191+09:00">that this perhaps was water flowing from the Great River of Yang-chou.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s9" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:31:49.586+09:00">They had a man mount the mast to see, and he reported</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s10" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:32:46.042+09:00">that [the whitish water] flowed from the northwest directly toward the south</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s11" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:33:00.486+09:00">and that its width was over twenty li</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s12" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:33:25.729+09:00">but that when one looked far along the way ahead the water again became light green.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s13" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:33:41.92+09:00">After we had proceeded for a short time,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s14" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:34:01.73+09:00">it turned out just as he had said.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s15" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:34:22.181+09:00">The Ambassador was greatly surprised that the color of the sea again became light green.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s16" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:35:27.59+09:00">The Korean lnterpreter, Kim Chongnam, stated</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s17" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:36:21.942+09:00">that he had heard it said that it was difficult to pass through the dug channel of Yang-chou</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s18" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:36:37.133+09:00">and that, since we bad already passed the whitish water,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR6v0299_CBETA_000-0005a1719.s19" xml:lang="en" resp="#schwermann" modified="2023-06-12T19:37:05.893+09:00">he suspected that we may have passed by the dug channel.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
